<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vermont_Progressive_Party&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The party lists Bernie Sanders as an elected progressive; however, Sanders is designated as an affiliated non-member.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Montpelier mayor <a href="/wiki/Anne_Watson" title="Anne Watson">Anne Watson</a> is officially elected to a non-partisan office; however, she is designated as a member of the party.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Watson is officially elected to a non-partisan office; however, she is designated as a member of the party.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
